CHAPTER 14. Nantucket.

(1968,8)more happen(2031,11)assage worthy the mentioning; so, after a
fine run, we safely arrived in(115,14)(127,8)! Take out your map and look at it. See what a real corner of
the world it occupies; how it stands there, away off shore, more lonely
than the Eddystone lighthouse. L(141,9)—a mere hillock, and elbow of
