long ages to come, an(832,12)always, as now; for be it Polar snow
or torrid sun, like a patent chronometer, hi(1994,11)vitality was
warranted to do well in all climates. Looking into his eyes, you seemed
to see there the yet lingering images(832,10)thousand-fold perils he
had calmly confronted through life. A staid, steadfa(1203,8)whose life
for the most part was a telling pantomime of action, and not a tame
