“It is not my intention, were it in my power, to enter(1741,10)inquiry
as to the true method of divi(1541,8) cetacea into groups and families.
* * * Utter confusion exists among the historians of this animal”
(sperm whale), says Surgeon Beale(257,9)39.

“Unfitness to pursue our research(1247,8)unfathomable waters.”
“Impenetrable veil covering our knowledge(602,9)etacea.” “A field
strewn(1034,8)orns.” “All these incomplete indications but serve to
torture us naturalists.”

Thus speak(848,13), the great Cuvier, and John Hunt(17,8)Lesson,
those lights of zoology and anatomy. Nevertheless, though of real
