“He smites his chest,” whispered Stubb, “(830,9)at for? methinks it
rings most vast, but hollow.”

“V(559,9)on a dumb brute!(2034,8)(2008,8), “that simply smote thee
from blindest instinct! Madness! To be enraged with(107,8)thing,
Captain Ahab, seems blasphemous.”

“Hark ye yet again—the (567,20)All visible objects, man,
are but as pasteboard masks. But in each event—in the living act, the
undoubted deed—there, some unknown but still reasoning thing puts forth
the mouldings of its features from behind the un(75,10)mask. If man
will strike, strike through the mask! How can the prisoner reach
outside except by thrusting(73,13)wall? To me,(1630,16) is
that wall, shoved near to me. Sometimes(1821,9)there’s naught beyond.
But ’tis enough. He tasks me; he heaps me; I see in him outrageous
strength, with an inscrutable malice sinewing it. That(37,12)
thing is chiefly what I hate; and(1168,8)(261,12)agent, or be the
(290,12)principal, I will wreak that hate upon him. Talk not to me
of(783,9)y, man; I’d(493,10)e sun if it insulted me. For could the
sun do that, then could I do the other; since there is ever a sort of
fair play herein, jealousy presiding over all creations. But not my
mast(1475,9)is even that (94,9). Who’s over me? Truth hath no
confines. Take off thine eye! more intolerable than fiends’ glarings is
a doltish stare! So, so(1698,9)ddenest and palest; my heat has melted
thee to anger-glow. But look ye(1787,10), what is said in heat, that
thing unsays itself. There are men from whom warm words are small
indignity. I meant(583,8)incense thee. Let it go. Look! see yonder
Turkish cheeks of spotted tawn—living, breathing pictures painted by
the sun. The Pagan leopards—(1231,8)cking and unworshipp(1322,9)s,
that live; and seek, and give no reasons for the torrid life they feel!
The crew, man, the crew! Are they not one and all with Ahab, in this
matter of the whale? See Stubb! he laughs! S(332,9) Chilian! he
snorts to think of it. Stand up amid the general hurricane, thy one
tost sapling cannot(604,10)! And(608,9)it? Reckon it. ’Tis but to
help(1579,8)a fin; no wondrous feat for(2044,9). W(85,9) more? From
