intervals, he would refer to piles of old log-books beside him, wherein
were set down the seasons and places in which, on(270,8) former
voyages of(26,9)ships, sperm whales had been captured or seen.

While thus employed, the heavy pewter lamp suspended in chains over his
head, continually rocked with the mo(739,8)the ship, and for ever
threw shifting gleam(499,10)ows of lines upon his(707,10)brow, till
it almost seemed that while he (656,8)was mark(790,8)(610,9)
