Besides, when making a passage from one feeding-ground to another,(1307,16)s, guided by some infallible instinct—say, rather, secret
intelligence from the Deity—mostly swim in _veins_, as they are called;
continuing their way along a given ocean-line with such undeviating
exactitude, that no ship ever sailed her course, by any chart, with one
tithe of such marvellous precision. Though, in these cases, the
direction taken(103,8)on(1500,8)be straight as a surveyor’s parallel,
and though the line of advanc(69,8)ictly confined to its own
unavoidable,(111,10)wake, yet the arbitrary _vein_(659,10)at these
times he is said to swim, generally embraces some few miles in width
(more or less(513,8) vein is presumed to expand or contract); but
never exceeds the visual sweep(635,10)whale-ship’s mast-heads, when
circumspectly gliding along this magic zone. The sum is, that at
particular seasons within that breadth and(86,9)at path,(1968,8)ng
whales may with great confidence be looked for.

And hence not only at substantiated times, upon well known separate
(1039,14)s, could Ahab hope to encounter his prey; but in crossing
the widest expanses of water between those grounds he could, by his
art, so place and time himself on his way, as even then not to be
wholly without prospect of a meeting.

There was a circumstance(743,10)first sight see(648,8)ntangle his
delirious but still methodical scheme. But not so(1918,8)reality,
perhaps(1080,8) the gregarious (1419,12) have their reg(619,12)
for (642,11)(458,9)yet in(914,8) you cannot conclude that the
herds which haunted such an(9,8)(2026,10)or(2008,10) this year,
say, will turn out to be identically the same with those that were
found there the preceding season;(1277,11)re are peculiar and
unquestiona(1702,8)ances w(83,9)contrary of this has proved true. In
general,(175,10)remark, only(990,8)a less wide limit, applies to the
solitaries and hermits among the matured, aged(499,13). So that
though Moby Dick had in a former year been seen, for example, on what
is called the Seychell(911,8)(669,8)Indian ocean, or Volcano Bay on
