This arrangement(213,9)(191,9)is necessary on two accounts. First:
In order to facilitate the fastening to it of an additional line from a
neighboring boat, in case the stricken whale should sound so deep as to
threaten to carry off the(1515,8)line originally attached to th(1470,9). In these instances,(819,10) of course is shifted like a mug
of ale, as(652,8),(481,10)one boa(611,9)other; though the first
