that I myself belong,(1078,8)but subordinately, to so emblazoned a
fraternity.

The gallant Perseus, a son of Jupiter, was the first whaleman; and to
the eternal honor of our calling be it said,(1299,10)(77,11)
attacked by our brotherhood(1453,9)kill(478,8)any sordid intent.
Those were the knightly days(144,8)profession, when we only bore arms
