no fairy’s arm can transcend it.

Five great(1244,9)ar(311,11)to it. First, when us(820,8)fin for
progression; Second(44,17)mace in battle; Third, in sweeping;
Fourth, in lobtailing; Fifth, in peaking flukes.

First: Being horizontal in its positi(824,8)L(2042,8)’s tail acts in a
different manner(1254,10)tails(738,8)other sea creatures. It never
wriggles. In man or fish, wriggling is a sign of inferiority. To the
whale, his tail(654,9)ole means of propulsion. Scroll-wise coiled
forwards beneath the body, and then rapidly sprung backwards, it is
this which gives that singular darting, leaping motion to the monster
when furiously swimming. His side-fins only serve to steer by.

Second: It is a little significant(894,9)ile one sperm whale only
fights another(32,13)with his head and jaw, nevertheless, in his
