CHAPTER 116. The Dying Whale.

Not seldom in this life, when, on the right side, fortune’s favourites
sail close by us, we, though all adroop before, catch somewha(1552,8)
rushing(708,9)and joyfully feel our bagging sails fill out. So(348,8)it with(689,11). For next day after encountering(1634,17),
