Epilogue

“AND I ONLY AM ESCAPED ALONE TO TELL THEE” Job.

The drama’s done. Why then here does any one step forth?—Because one
did survive the wreck.

It so(881,8), that after the Parsee’s disappearance, I was he whom the
Fates ordained to take the place(635,8)’s bowsman, when that(19,8)
assumed the vacant post; the same, who, when(1963,8)last day the three
men were tossed from(1766,8)the rocking boat, was dropped astern. So,
(1963,10)n the margin(1852,8)ensuing scene(1249,8) full sight of it,
when the halfspent suctio(74,9)sunk ship reached m(355,9)then, but
slowly, drawn towards the closing vortex. When I(77,9)it, it had
subsided to a creamy pool. Round and round, then, and ever contracting
(125,12)button-like black bubble(2025,8)axis of that slowly
wheeling circle, like another Ixion I did revolve. Till, gain(1461,8)
vital centre, th(128,15)upward burst; and now, liberated by
reason of its cunning spring, and, owing to its great buoyancy, rising
with great force, the coffin life-buoy shot lengthwise from(1106,8),
fell ov(1309,8)floated by my side. Buoyed up by that coffin, for almost
one whole day and night, I(84,9)on a soft and dirgelike main. The
unharming sharks, they glided by as if with padlocks on their mouths;
the(1852,8)sea-hawks sailed with sheathed beaks. On the second day, a
sail drew near, near(1603,8)picked me up at last. It(828,8)
devious-cruising Rachel, that in her retracing search after her missing
children, only found(690,9)orphan.




